@page "/about"
@layout Components.Layout.PublicLayout
@attribute [AllowAnonymous]
@attribute [ExcludeFromInteractiveRouting]

@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authorization
@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Web

<!-- Hero -->
<section class="pub-page-hero">
    <h1 class="pub-gradient-text">Manufacturing, Reimagined</h1>
    <p class="pub-page-hero-sub">We build software for the people who build things.</p>
</section>

<!-- Mission -->
<section class="pub-section">
    <div class="pub-about-mission pub-fade-up">
        <h2 class="pub-section-title">Our Mission</h2>
        <p class="pub-about-text">
            Additive manufacturing is transforming how products are made &mdash; but the software running most shops
            hasn't kept up. Spreadsheets, whiteboards, and generic ERP systems weren't designed for the realities of
            SLS print scheduling, multi-stage production tracking, or build plate optimization.
        </p>
        <p class="pub-about-text">
            Vectrik was founded by manufacturing engineers who lived these problems every day. We're building the MES
            platform we always wished existed: one that understands changeover timing, operator shift windows, and the
            unique flow of additive production from powder to shipped part.
        </p>
        <p class="pub-about-text">
            Our goal is simple &mdash; give every additive manufacturer the intelligence tools to schedule smarter,
            execute faster, and deliver on time, every time.
        </p>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- Our Story -->
<section class="pub-section pub-section-alt">
    <div class="pub-about-mission pub-fade-up">
        <h2 class="pub-section-title">Our Story</h2>
        <p class="pub-about-text">
            Vectrik was born on the shop floor. Our founders spent years running SLS metal printing operations &mdash;
            scheduling builds on whiteboards, tracking changeovers in spreadsheets, and scrambling to answer auditors
            with binders full of paper records. They evaluated every MES on the market and found the same problem
            everywhere: software built for traditional subtractive manufacturing, awkwardly retrofitted for additive.
        </p>
        <p class="pub-about-text">
            None of those systems understood that SLS builds run overnight unattended. None could model cooldown
            chamber capacity or predict when a changeover would land outside an operator's shift. None handled
            the reality that a single build plate carries parts from multiple work orders at different stack heights.
        </p>
        <p class="pub-about-text">
            So they built Vectrik &mdash; the MES platform they always wished existed. Designed from the ground up
            for additive manufacturing, it bridges the gap between traditional production management and the unique
            demands of metal 3D printing. Every feature reflects real production experience, not theoretical workflows.
        </p>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- By the Numbers -->
<section class="pub-section">
    <h2 class="pub-section-title pub-fade-up">By the Numbers</h2>
    <div class="pub-metrics-grid">
        <div class="pub-metric pub-fade-up">
            <span class="pub-metric-value pub-gradient-text">15+</span>
            <span class="pub-metric-label">Production stages supported</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pub-metric pub-fade-up">
            <span class="pub-metric-value pub-gradient-text">10+</span>
            <span class="pub-metric-label">Machine types configurable</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pub-metric pub-fade-up">
            <span class="pub-metric-value pub-gradient-text">24/7</span>
            <span class="pub-metric-label">Continuous operation support</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pub-metric pub-fade-up">
            <span class="pub-metric-value pub-gradient-text">100%</span>
            <span class="pub-metric-label">Part traceability</span>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- Values -->
<section class="pub-section pub-section-alt">
    <h2 class="pub-section-title pub-fade-up">What We Stand For</h2>
    <div class="pub-feature-grid pub-feature-grid-3">
        <div class="pub-card pub-fade-up">
            <div class="pub-card-icon">
                <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                    <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/>
                    <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="6"/>
                    <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="2"/>
                </svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="pub-card-title">Precision</h3>
            <p class="pub-card-text">
                We hold our software to the same tolerances our customers hold their parts. Every feature is
                engineered with care &mdash; no bloat, no guesswork, no shortcuts. If it's in the platform,
                it works the way a manufacturing engineer expects it to.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="pub-card pub-fade-up">
            <div class="pub-card-icon">
                <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                    <path d="M12 2a7 7 0 017 7c0 5-7 13-7 13S5 14 5 9a7 7 0 017-7z"/>
                    <circle cx="12" cy="9" r="2.5"/>
                    <path d="M9 22h6"/>
                </svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="pub-card-title">Intelligence</h3>
            <p class="pub-card-text">
                Data should drive decisions, not just fill dashboards. Our platform turns raw production data
                into actionable recommendations &mdash; from build plate composition to changeover timing to
                delivery risk predictions.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="pub-card pub-fade-up">
            <div class="pub-card-icon">
                <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                    <polyline points="22 12 18 12 15 21 9 3 6 12 2 12"/>
                </svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="pub-card-title">Reliability</h3>
            <p class="pub-card-text">
                Your machines run 24/7 &mdash; your MES should too. We architect for uptime, build for resilience,
                and support with urgency. When production depends on your software, there's no room for downtime.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- Built for AM -->
<section class="pub-section">
    <div class="pub-about-mission pub-fade-up">
        <h2 class="pub-section-title">Built for Additive</h2>
        <p class="pub-about-text">
            Unlike generic MES platforms retrofitted for 3D printing, Vectrik was designed from day one around the
            unique workflows of additive manufacturing. We understand that SLS builds run overnight, that changeovers
            depend on operator availability, that build plates hold multiple parts from different orders, and that
            production flows through depowdering, EDM, machining, and finishing before a part ships.
        </p>
        <p class="pub-about-text">
            Every feature in the platform reflects real production experience. Our scheduling engine accounts for
            cooldown chamber capacity. Our advisor knows that stacking parts changes print duration. Our stage tracking
            handles both build-level and part-level operations seamlessly.
        </p>
    </div>
</section>

